    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="877"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/422.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Letters of authorization having been received, the loan issue should now proceed
                    rapidly. Meanwhile it is impossible to prevent, provisionally, double payment of
                    interest. Until the Erlanger loan is finally terminated, remittance must be made
                    as usual. This advance will ultimately be returned to Liberia. Double payment is
                    provisional only.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
